      "side": 1,
      "message": "Agreed about the comment - I\u0027ll try to figure out what it should say.\n\nCurrently: readPixels (on any type) does not respect color space. I think that should be changed, but that\u0027s a much bigger refactor.\n\ncopyTo (with the current signature) only has two options:\n1) Do not respect color space (which is what happens now and with this change).\n2) Respect color space by applying a heuristic to guess a valid color space for the dest. I don\u0027t like this idea.\n\nMy global preference: copyTo does not respect color space, or has a signature update so that it can. readPixels does respect color space.",
      "parentUuid": "66ba4639_78aeb5d0",
